# Quick Start

Get up and running with the Lunaby API in minutes.

<CodeBlock
  title="Install the Lunaby SDK with npm"
  tabs={[{ id: "npm", label: "npm", language: "bash", code: "npm install lunaby-sdk" }]}
/>

## Make your first request

Here's how to make your first request using the Lunaby SDK.

<CodeBlock
  tabs={[
    {
      id: "python",
      label: "Python",
      language: "python",
      code: "from openai import OpenAI\n\nclient = OpenAI(\n    api_key=\"YOUR_API_KEY\",\n    base_url=\"https://api.lunie.dev/v1\"\n)\n\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"lunaby-pro\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello!\"}]\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)"
    },
    {
      id: "js",
      label: "Javascript",
      language: "javascript",
      code: "import Lunaby from 'lunaby-sdk';\n\nconst client = new Lunaby({\n    apiKey: process.env.LUNABY_API_KEY,\n});\n\nconst response = await client.chat.create([\n    { role: 'user', content: 'Hello!' }\n]);\nconsole.log(response.data.choices[0].message.content);"
    },
    {
      id: "curl",
      label: "cURL",
      language: "bash",
      code: "curl https://api.lunie.dev/v1/chat/completions \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"model\": \"lunaby-pro\",\n    \"messages\": [\n      {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\"},\n      {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello!\"}\n    ]\n  }'"
    }
  ]}
/>

# Chat Completions

Create chat completions using the Lunaby API.

<CodeBlock
  tabs={[
    {
      id: "python",
      label: "Python",
      language: "python",
      code: "response = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"lunaby-pro\",\n    messages=[\n        {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\"},\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello!\"}\n    ]\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)"
    },
    {
      id: "js",
      label: "Javascript",
      language: "javascript",
      code: "const response = await client.chat.create([\n    { role: 'system', content: 'You are a helpful assistant.' },\n    { role: 'user', content: 'Hello!' }\n], {\n    model: 'lunaby-pro',\n});\n\nconsole.log(response.data.choices[0].message.content);"
    }
  ]}
/>

# Streaming

Stream responses in real-time for a better user experience.

<CodeBlock
  tabs={[
    {
      id: "python",
      label: "Python",
      language: "python",
      code: "stream = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"lunaby-pro\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Tell me a story\"}],\n    stream=True,\n)\nfor chunk in stream:\n    print(chunk.choices[0].delta.content or \"\", end=\"\")"
    },
    {
      id: "js",
      label: "Javascript",
      language: "javascript",
      code: "for await (const chunk of client.chat.stream([\n  { role: 'user', content: 'Tell me a story' }\n])) {\n  const content = chunk.choices[0].delta.content;\n  if (content) {\n    process.stdout.write(content);\n  }\n}"
    }
  ]}
/>

# Vision (Image Generation)

Generate stunning images from text descriptions using the Lunaby Vision model.

<CodeBlock
  tabs={[
    {
      id: "python",
      label: "Python",
      language: "python",
      code: "response = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"lunaby-vision\",\n    messages=[\n        {\n            \"role\": \"user\", \n            \"content\": \"A cyberpunk city in neon rain, 8k resolution\"\n        }\n    ]\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)"
    },
    {
      id: "js",
      label: "Javascript",
      language: "javascript",
      code: "const response = await client.images.generate('A cyberpunk city', {\n  model: 'lunaby-vision',\n});\nconst base64 = response.data.data[0].b64_json;"
    }
  ]}
/>
